											<section class="main bio authorbio">
							<h3 class="invis">Author bio</h3>
																																															<a href="https://hakaimagazine.com/profiles/erica-gies/" class="tagmanager" id="author_link_bottom" >
											<div class="container col3 ">
												<div class="col span2"><p>Erica Gies is the author of <em>Water Always Wins: Thriving in an Age of Drought and Deluge</em> and an independent journalist who covers water, climate change, critters, and more from Victoria, British Columbia, and San Francisco, California. Her work appears in <em>Scientific American</em>, <em>National Geographic</em>, the <em>New York Times</em>, <em>Nature</em>, <em>bioGraphic</em>, Ensia, <em>The Economist</em>, and other outlets.</p></div>
												<div class="singlebioimage col nomobile"><img width="520" height="503" src="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/red_jacket_head-520x503.jpg" class="attachment-medium size-medium wp-post-image" alt="" decoding="async" srcset="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/red_jacket_head-520x503.jpg 520w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/red_jacket_head.jpg 720w" sizes="(max-width: 520px) 100vw, 520px" /></div>
											</div>
											</a>
